# WhatsApp Bot — Starter scaffold

This repository is a minimal starter for a modular WhatsApp bot (Node.js). It is intentionally small so you can add a WhatsApp library (Baileys, whatsapp-web.js, venom, etc.) and build plugins/commands later.

Features
- Plugin-based architecture (drop-in modules in `src/plugins/`)
- Environment-configured
- Dockerfile for deployment to Spaceify or any Docker-based panel

Getting started (local)
1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill values.
2. Install dependencies:
   npm install
3. Run:
   npm start

Note: This scaffold does not include a WhatsApp client library by default. Add your preferred library and implement connect/authorize logic inside `src/adapter.js` or directly in `src/index.js`.

Project structure
- src/
  - index.js         — app bootstrap, plugin loader
  - adapter.example.js — where to integrate WhatsApp client (placeholder)
  - plugins/
    - echo.js         — example plugin

Deployment
- Docker: build and run the image
  docker build -t whatsapp-bot .
  docker run --env-file .env -p 3000:3000 whatsapp-bot

Spaceify / other panels
- Most panels accept Docker images. Use the included Dockerfile.
- Ensure your panel provides persistent storage (for session files) and env vars.

Next steps
1. Choose a WhatsApp library (Baileys recommended for headless server bots).
2. Implement authentication/session persistence in `src/adapter.example.js`.
3. Add commands/plugins to `src/plugins/` that export a known shape (see example).

